== Rice ==

Bring a #medium saucepan{} of @water{} to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Halve the @green pepper{1}, remove and discard the core and seeds. Chop into
small chunks.

Drain and rinse the @kidney beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

When the water is boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for
~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Chilli ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high
heat.

When hot, add the pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, for ~{3%minutes}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{2%tbsp} and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook,
stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10g}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and
garlic{1%400g can}, @BBQ sauce{32%g} and kidney beans. Add a pinch of
@sugar{pinch} if you have some.

Bring to the boil and stir to combine. Lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

== Zesty Creme Fraiche ==

Meanwhile, put the @soured cream{75%g} into a #small bowl{}.

Grate in the @lime{1/2}(zested), mix well and season to taste with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Chop the lime into wedges.

== To Serve ==

Stir the @baby spinach{100%g} through the chilli, a handful at a time until wilted
and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season the chilli to taste with salt and pepper. Add a splash of @water{} to
loosen if you like.

Serve the rice in bowls topped with the veggie chilli.

Add a spoonful of the zesty creme fraiche and finish with the lime wedges for
squeezing over. Enjoy!